news.title: Endangered and endemic: Madagascar’s lemurs susceptible to coronavirus infection
news.summary: Certain species of lemurs in Madagascar share a similar enzyme receptor to humans that could make them susceptible to contracting SARS-CoV-2, the virus that causes COVID-19, a study shows.

news.title: Can whales and dolphins catch COVID-19 from wastewater? It’s murky
news.summary: A new study identifies 15 marine mammal species, including whales, dolphins, seals and sea otters, that could be susceptible to the SARS-CoV-2 virus through contact with wastewater.
